transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: Hello, how are we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I want to know, where do I go by to cancel an order?

Speaker 2: It was automatic refill, evidently, that they sent me.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Let me have the phone that you used for your prescription, please.

Speaker 1: The number?

Speaker 2: Phone number, phone number that you used.

Speaker 1: Oh, 202-308-7354.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Mr. Whitefield?

Speaker 2: Whitfield, yes.

Speaker 1: Whitfield.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: In D.C.?

Speaker 2: Washington, D.C.?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: So what I see is you have a prescription for 100 milligrams, 10 tablets,

Speaker 1: and I think because you got 10 tablets, there was 30 days in the month,

Speaker 2: assuming you asked if they got you on a refill, but if you don't need it,

Speaker 1: I'm going to advise the pharmacy to stop the initial writing,

Speaker 2: and you can just order as needed.

Speaker 1: They pause the prescription up to half a year,

Speaker 2: so you don't get it on the monthly anymore, and you can just reorder.

Speaker 1: So that allows you to lock your pricing and keep your doctor prescription

Speaker 2: available to you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: But what if I just want to cancel it?

Speaker 1: It's up to you, sir.

Speaker 2: It's up to you, sir.

Speaker 1: If you're sure that you will not need Viagra, but you have, like I said,

Speaker 2: they want me to let you know that, you know,

Speaker 1: you have the option to pause when you don't need to receive refill

Speaker 2: or get bill every month.

Speaker 1: You're not obligated to do that.

Speaker 2: That's just the initial writing, assuming that you need Viagra.

Speaker 1: But when you don't need it as often, everything is paused,

Speaker 2: and you reorder as needed, and you don't pay market price when you reorder.

Speaker 1: You keep the same price you have today, and then, you know,

Speaker 2: you reorder in a few months or whatever when you need it.

Speaker 1: But they don't require you to get you every month.

Speaker 2: We want to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Excuse me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Another question.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: They automatically sent me one.

Speaker 2: What if I want to send the one they sent?

Speaker 1: Can you send it back?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: If you want, you can send it back, and then we're going to refund you, okay?

Speaker 2: And I'll cancel your prescription, cancel your account.

Speaker 1: Be aware that, you know, you might not be able to reorder,

Speaker 2: or if the order goes through, you will have a different price,

Speaker 1: because they're going to have to get you a new doctor consultation,

Speaker 2: which costs money to the company,

Speaker 1: because we didn't preserve and save the one they financed for you.

Speaker 2: So that's what I was trying to do, so you could get Viagra in the future.

Speaker 1: But I canceled it.

Speaker 2: I canceled your account.

Speaker 1: And if you want to return it, you can just return it,

Speaker 2: and then we're going to refund you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So I already got the paper to resend it.

Speaker 1: I mean, I got to get it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you just write refuse return on the package.

Speaker 1: Refuse return on the package.

Speaker 2: That's all you got to do.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And take it to the mailbox and send it back, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can't even leave it in your mailbox.

Speaker 2: When the mailman see that, he's going to understand.

Speaker 1: He's got to send that back to the source.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, then.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: How long is it going to take to get his refund?

Speaker 2: As soon as we get the package back, ma'am.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, does he need to send it certified or just put refuse on it?

Speaker 1: I already explained to you the process, ma'am.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: No, they just send it back with the package and just say refuse.

Speaker 2: Did he sign up for automatic refills before y'all sent that package?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: So basically, the doctor wrote the prescription because he ordered 10 with

Speaker 1: refills, but when you don't need refills, when you call us,

Speaker 2: we advise the pharmacy that you're not really an active patient like that,

Speaker 1: so we stop the initial writing from the doctor and you order as needed.

Speaker 2: That's what I was offering,

Speaker 1: which allow you to save and order at the same price in the future.

Speaker 2: We're just preserving the doctor consultation.

Speaker 1: The account is paused, so you just order as needed.

Speaker 2: But he said that he don't want to keep his prescription,

Speaker 1: so I cancel everything.

Speaker 2: The whole account is canceled,

Speaker 1: so he might not be able to reorder in the future,

Speaker 2: or if he does reorder, price will be different.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay, then.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
